Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and remove the core 
and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @green beans{150} then chop into thirds.

Add the @egg noodle nest{2} to a #saucepan{}, cover with boiling water and pop on 
medium high heat. Simmer until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}, drizzle 
with @oil{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the 
@diced chicken breast{260%g}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry until 
golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the pepper and green beans. Stir-fry until the chicken 
is cooked, another ~{5-6%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Lower the heat to medium, stir in the @ketjap manis{25%g}, 1 tbsp water per person, 
the @chow mein paste{1} and @chow mein garnish{1}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute} to 
dissolve.

Add the noodles and stir through until piping hot.

> Add a splash of water if you feel it needs loosening up.

Serve the chicken chow mein in #bowls{}. Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen to receive diced chicken breast instead of diced 
> chicken thigh, just cook it the same way the recipe tells you to cook the 
> diced thigh in the step above and in the rest of the recipe.